The article discusses the importance of immigrants in the United States and their contributions to the country. It highlights that immigrants work in various industries, create businesses, and generate millions of jobs. They are also essential workers, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, and have played a significant role in science, technology, innovation, arts, culture, and government. The Biden Administration is committed to ensuring an accessible and humane immigration system, removing barriers to immigration benefits, and addressing discrimination and violence faced by immigrants. The United States has historically been a refuge for those seeking safe haven, and the government continues to welcome and provide support to vulnerable migrant populations. The article emphasizes the value of diversity and inclusion, and encourages people to learn about the history of immigrant communities and observe National Immigrant Heritage Month.